Compile:
cd src
make

Running the Program:
After the program is compiled there are two methods of running the program.

    Method-1:
    this method will generate 25 input files containing for each of the input sizes requested(10,100,1000), the text file containing individual run times, and a text file
    containing the avg run time for each input size.

        Ensure that there is a directory called data in the directory above src.
        make generate_files
        make process_files

    Method-2:
    this method allows you to provide an input and output file.
        ./Hopkins_Brent_Quicksort InputFilePath OutputFilePath

Clean Up:
make clean will remove all text files in the data directory.
